law.text:
Each application for a title pledge lending license shall be filed with the department, and the application shall provide the following:
The name of the beneficial owner if a sole proprietorship; or in the case of a corporation, all individuals serving as officers or directors; or in the case of a partnership or limited liability company, the members thereof;
The street address where the title pledge office is to be operated;
Proof of the capital and surety bond requirements set forth in KRS 286.10-215, accompanied by an unaudited financial statement from a certified public accountant;
An affidavit from each individual set forth in subsection (1) of this section stating that each individual has not been convicted of a felony within the ten (10) year period preceding the date of application;
Certified funds in the amount of five hundred dollars ($500) payable to the department; and
Other information as required by the commissioner.
